# ============================================================
# CURSOR RULES — React Native + Ignite Boilerplate
# Figma → Code Workflow
# ============================================================
# This file is read by Cursor before every generation.
# Keep it updated as your project evolves.
# ============================================================

## PROJECT IDENTITY
- App name: DevTask (or replace with your app name)
- Framework: React Native (bare workflow)
- Boilerplate: Ignite (by Infinite Red)
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Navigation: React Navigation v6 (stack + bottom tabs)
- State: MobX-State-Tree (Ignite default) OR Zustand (replace if different)
- Styling: StyleSheet.create ONLY — no inline styles, no styled-components
- Backend: Firebase Auth + Realtime Database

## DIRECTORY RULES — ALWAYS follow Ignite structure
```
src/
  app/             # Navigation stacks
  components/      # Shared reusable components
  screens/         # One folder per screen
    HomeScreen/
      index.tsx
      HomeScreen.styles.ts   # Always separate styles file
  models/          # MobX-State-Tree models
  services/        # API, Firebase, storage
  theme/
    colors.ts      # ONLY source of color values
    spacing.ts     # ONLY source of spacing values
    typography.ts  # ONLY source of font sizes/weights
  utils/
  hooks/
```

## COMPONENT RULES
- Functional components only — no class components
- Every component must be typed with a Props interface
- Export named exports, not default exports (except screens)
- Never import colors/spacing as raw numbers — always use theme tokens
- Every touchable must have an `accessibilityLabel`
- Use `Pressable` not `TouchableOpacity` for new components

## STYLING RULES — CRITICAL
- NEVER hardcode colors: ❌ color: '#1A73E8' → ✅ color: colors.primary
- NEVER hardcode spacing: ❌ padding: 16 → ✅ padding: spacing.md
- NEVER hardcode font sizes: ❌ fontSize: 16 → ✅ fontSize: typography.body
- All StyleSheet.create calls go in a separate *.styles.ts file
- Use `flex: 1` for full-screen containers
- Always set backgroundColor on screen root views

## FIGMA → CODE TRANSLATION RULES
- When given Figma specs, extract exact values and map to the nearest theme token
- If a value doesn't exist in theme, ADD it to the theme file and use the token
- Figma Auto Layout → flexDirection + gap (use gap property, RN 0.71+)
- Figma padding (top/right/bottom/left) → paddingVertical/paddingHorizontal if symmetric
- Figma corner radius → borderRadius
- Figma opacity → opacity prop (not color alpha)
- Figma text styles → map to typography tokens

## SCREEN GENERATION RULES
- Every screen gets its own folder: src/screens/[ScreenName]/
- Required files per screen: index.tsx + [ScreenName].styles.ts
- Screen component must accept navigation prop typed with NavigationProp
- Wrap screen in SafeAreaView from react-native-safe-area-context
- Add a useHeader() call or set navigation options in useEffect
- Never fetch data directly in the screen — use a custom hook or store action

## FIREBASE RULES
- Auth logic lives in src/services/firebase/auth.ts
- Database reads/writes in src/services/firebase/database.ts
- Never call Firebase directly from a screen or component
- Always handle loading, success, and error states

## CODE QUALITY
- No `any` types — use proper TypeScript
- No console.log in production code (use a logger utility)
- Destructure props at the top of every component
- Use optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??) — never assume data exists
- Every list must have a keyExtractor

## WHAT NOT TO DO
- Do not install new packages without asking first
- Do not modify theme files unless explicitly asked
- Do not use Animated API directly — prefer Reanimated 2
- Do not create barrel exports (index.ts re-exports) unless asked
- Do not use React.FC — use explicit function declarations
